# Quick Reference: Ablation Studies & Reproducibility

## Running the System

### 1. Standard Run (HYBRID Mode, Default)
```powershell
Set-Location "d:\Mtech Main project\smartgrid-audit-base"
python.exe -m smartgrid_mas.run_all
# Output: logs/N100/summary.json, logs/N200/summary.json, logs/N500/summary.json
```

### 2. Single Scalability Point (N=100 only, 24-hour cycle)
```powershell
$env:SMARTGRID_SWEEP="100"
python.exe -m smartgrid_mas.run_all
# Output: logs/N100/summary.json (~10 minutes)
```

### 3. Ablation Study: All Three Modes (N=100)
```powershell
$env:SMARTGRID_SWEEP="100"
$env:SMARTGRID_ABLATION="HYBRID,RL_ONLY,GRADIENT_ONLY"
python.exe -m smartgrid_mas.run_all
# Output: logs/N100/summary.json with ablation_modes.{HYBRID,RL_ONLY,GRADIENT_ONLY}
```

### 4. Seed Robustness (3 Seeds, N=100, HYBRID)
```powershell
$env:SMARTGRID_SWEEP="100"
$env:SMARTGRID_SEEDS="42,123,999"
python.exe -m smartgrid_mas.run_all
# Output: logs/seed_42/summary.json, logs/seed_123/summary.json, logs/seed_999/summary.json
#         with seed_robustness_analysis aggregation
```

### 5. Full Ablation × Scalability Grid (3 modes × 3 Ns = 9 runs, ~10 hours)
```powershell
$env:SMARTGRID_SWEEP="100,200,500"
$env:SMARTGRID_ABLATION="HYBRID,RL_ONLY,GRADIENT_ONLY"
python.exe -m smartgrid_mas.run_all
# Output: logs/N{100,200,500}/summary.json with full ablation comparisons
```

### 6. Fast Prototyping (1-hour cycles instead of 24h)
```powershell
$env:SMARTGRID_SWEEP="100"
$env:SMARTGRID_CYCLE_HOURS="1"
$env:SMARTGRID_ABLATION="HYBRID,RL_ONLY"
python.exe -m smartgrid_mas.run_all
# Output: logs/N100/summary.json (1 hour per mode, 2 hours total)
```

