## Failure Mode Detection

### Event Logging

The system logs failure events during constraint enforcement. Check for these patterns:

```
FAILURE_MODE: budget_exhaustion | high_risk_agents_denied={N} | ...
FAILURE_MODE: audit_count_exhaustion | high_risk_agents_denied={N} | ...
```

**Example:** Find all budget exhaustion events in N=500 run:
```powershell
Get-Content "logs\N500\*.log" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-String "budget_exhaustion"
```

**Interpretation:**
- N=100: 0 events (adequate budget for all high-risk agents)
- N=200: 3-8 events (occasional budget pressure)
- N=500: 47-94 events (frequent constraints triggered)

